[1] Oregon (Lane County, Washington County): Portland airport transmission
Date: Mon 28 Oct 2019
Source: KLCC/Centers for Disease Control [abridged, edited]
https://www.klcc.org/post/lane-county-resident-diagnosed-measles


A Lane County resident and a visitor to Washington County have been diagnosed with measles. Their illnesses are linked to an individual with the disease who passed through Portland International Airport earlier this month [October 2019].

According to the Oregon Health Authority (OHA), the 2 new cases reportedly were on the same international flight that landed in Portland on [12 Oct 2019], as reported by Multnomah County Health Department. OHA epidemiologists are working with public health staff in both counties to confirm sites where others may have been exposed.

None of the people involved in this case had been fully vaccinated against measles.

[byline: Love Cross]

--
communicated by:
ProMED-mail from HealthMap Alerts
<promed@promedmail.org>

[The announcement comes toward the end of a historic year for measles cases in the north western United States and across the country. The Centers for Disease Control and Prevention has counted at least 1250 cases, including 86 cases in Washington. Oregon has seen a total of 27 cases, including these 2 new cases (https://www.opb.org/news/article/measles-oregon-portland-airport-pdx-exposure-sites/).]

