[5] Samoa: situational update no. 2
Date: Wed 30 Oct 2019
Source: Government of Samoa via ReliefWeb [abridged, edited]
https://reliefweb.int/report/samoa/situational-update-no-2-measles-cases-presenting-until-27-october-2019-date-report-30


Key points:
- As of [27 Oct 2019] there have been 314 suspected measles cases with 15 confirmed cases and 146 laboratory results pending;
- to date, there [have] been 3 related [mortalities]; a 14 month old, [an] 8 month old and a 37 year old -- all are highly suspected measles [cases], awaiting laboratory confirmation;
- of the 314 cases, [the] majority, 56% (176), are children under 4 years of age;
- 79% (249) of suspected cases reside in Upolu and 18% (57) in Savaii;
- 29% (91) of the 314 suspected cases have been admitted to hospital, 96% were admitted at TTMH [Tupua Tamasese Meaole Hospital] with one transferred from Savaii, 4% (4); the majority of admissions are less than 5 years old with 3 pregnant mothers (2 at TTMH and 1 at MTII [Malietoa Tanumafili II] Hospital, Savaii).

