A 2nd warning over measles has been issued to passengers who sailed on the NorthLink ferry on 3 dates earlier this month [October 2019] after a 2nd case was confirmed. NHS Shetland says it is working with other relevant authorities, including Health Protection Scotland, to ensure all control measures are in place to prevent further spread of the disease.

[byline: Ryan Taylor]

